{
  "local_port": 40894,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the procedure to apply to an RTI?",
  "response": "Applying for information under the Right to Information (RTI) Act in India is a straightforward process. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you apply:\n\n### 1. **Identify the Public Authority**\n   - Determine the specific government department, ministry, or public authority that holds the information you are seeking.\n\n### 2. **Draft the RTI Application**\n   - **Language**: The application can be written in English, Hindi, or the official language of the area.\n   - **Details to Include**:\n     - Your name, address, and contact information.\n     - Specify the information you are seeking. Be clear and precise.\n     - If you want the information in a particular format (e.g., photocopy, digital copy, etc.), mention it.\n     - Mention if you belong to the below poverty line (BPL) category, as you may be exempt from the fee.\n   - **Tips**:\n     - Limit the application to one subject matter to avoid confusion.\n     - Keep the application concise and to the point.\n\n### 3. **Pay the Application Fee**\n   - **Fee**: \u20b910 for most applicants. The fee can be paid via Indian Postal Order (IPO), demand draft, or cash (if submitting in person).\n   - **BPL Category**: If you belong to the BPL category, you are exempt from the fee. Attach a copy of your BPL certificate.\n\n### 4. **Submit the Application**\n   - **In Person**: Submit the application to the Public Information Officer (PIO) of the concerned department.\n   - **By Post**: Send the application via registered post or speed post to the PIO\u2019s office.\n   - **Online**: Many government departments and states have online portals for RTI applications. You can submit your application through these portals (e.g., [RTI Online Portal](https://rtionline.gov.in/)).\n\n### 5. **Acknowledgement and Tracking**\n   - **Acknowledgement**: If you submit in person or online, ensure you receive an acknowledgment receipt.\n   - **Tracking**: Keep track of your application\u2019s status using the unique registration number provided.\n\n### 6. **Receive the Information**\n   - **Response Time**: The PIO is required to respond within 30 days of receiving the application (or 48 hours if it concerns life or liberty).\n   - **Information Provided**: You will receive the information in the format you requested, or the PIO will inform you if the information cannot be provided.\n\n### 7. **Appeal (if necessary)**\n   - **First Appeal**: If you are not satisfied with the response or if no response is received within the stipulated time, you can file a first appeal with the First Appellate Authority (FAA) within 30 days.\n   - **Second Appeal**: If the first appeal does not resolve the issue, you can file a second appeal with the Central Information Commission (CIC) or State Information Commission (SIC) within 90 days.\n\n### Important Points:\n- **No Need to Specify the Reason**: You do not need to provide a reason for seeking the information.\n- **Keep Records**: Maintain copies of your application, fee payment proof, and receipts for future reference.\n\nBy following these steps, you can effectively apply for information under the RTI Act and exercise your right to access government-held information.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
